Name: MSDK Encoding H265
Description: To validate the fixed function hardware accelerated H.265 video encoding in MSDK
Test Environment:
1. Download and install the latest Simics
2. startx &
Step Expected Result:
1. Video encoding success.
2. Video playback will not be smooth due to simics limitation
3. Video playback has no corruption.
4. System does not hang or freeze.

Name: H265 Video Encoding - Progressive stream, Profile: high, Level: 3, Bitrate: 3000 kbps, Framerate: 30 fps, Format: H265, Width: 640, Height: 480, Rate Control: constant, Target Usage: Balanced
Test Environment:
1. Download and install the latest SW BKC image
2. Install the latest Media SDK Driver
3. Install the latest UFO Driver
4. Install the latest MSDK Package
5. Start Weston with the following command:
? export LIBVA_DRIVERS_PATH=/usr/lib64
? export LIBVA_DRIVER_NAME=iHD
? export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/intel/mediasdk/samples/_bin/x64
? export XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/tmp/
? weston --tty=2 --idle-time=0 &
Step Expected Result:
1.	Video FPS does not drop.
2.	Video playback is smooth.
3.	Video playback has no corruption.
4.	System does not hang or freeze.
5.	Encoding successful
